-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Rio Cristal, Southern Copper
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-06-12T21:00:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-12/peru-stocks-buenaventura-rio-cristal-southern-copper.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a third session, dropping
0.1 percent to 20,887.63. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed
0.5 percent to 2,721.37.  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian zinc
exploration company, fell 11 percent to 8 cents, a two-year low,
after zinc futures declined in  London .  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper
producer, dropped 1.1 percent to $29.45 after copper declined in
 New York , said  Francisco Miranda , an analyst at Lima-based
investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, rose 1.2 percent to $41 after
gold gained for a third session in New York.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner, rose
1 percent to $4.17.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
